{
  "resourceType": "Questionnaire",
  "name": "CareScore",
  "title": "CARE Score for Acute Coronary Syndrome",
  "status": "active",
  "subjectType": "Patient",
  "description": "Bedside, troponin-independent rule-out tool for acute coronary syndrome in ED chest-pain patients. The CARE rule is the four-component (History, ECG, Age, Risk factors) subset of the HEART Score; a score ≤ 1 ('negative CARE') supports safe early discharge without biomarker testing. Source: Moumneh T et al., Intern Emerg Med 2018;13(7):1111–1119.",
  "item": [
    {
